The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Ceat sells Mumbai land for Rs 130cr
                                                                                                               Ceat sells Mumbai land for Rs 130cr
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                               
	Mumbai, March 10: Ceat Ltd, the flagship company of the RPG group, today sold seven acres of land at Bhandup in Mumbai for Rs 130 crore.         
	The company signed an agreement with Ashford InfoTech Ltd for development of the land located at Village Road in Bhandup, a suburb in Mumbai.         
	Ceat said the proceeds of the land sale would be used to fund its expansion plans. The company added that the transaction would not impact tyre manufacturing or affect its workforce as the present operations would continue in the remaining 24 acres near the same location.         
	Ceat makes tyres for all segments that include heavy duty trucks and buses, light commercial vehicles, earth movers, forklifts, tractors, trailers, cars, two and three-wheelers. It has manufacturing facilities in Mumbai, Nashik and Kerala, apart from two Sri Lankan plants.         
	Ceat was the first Indian tyre company to set up facilities outside India. It is the market leader in Sri Lanka.         
	Ceat exports tyres to over 100 countries and is looking to enter newer markets.         
	The companys exports stood at Rs 412 crore in the last financial year.                                                                                                                                        
